Subject: [TikTok] Office Hours
Description:
Hi All,

You are all invited to attend TikTok Office Hours! This is a safe space for everyone and anyone to share any observations that they've noticed on the platform, ask questions, and even brainstorm - so come join the party at the Zoom link below and let's talk about all things Tok-related.

Join Zoom Meeting: https://vaynerx.zoom.us/j/8491633269
________________________________________________________
AGENDA:
  • :30 minutes | All Things TikTok: observations, Q&A, brainstorming, etc..
    • An open floor for anybody to ask questions, brainstorm with the group, share wins, and state any observations that are happening on the platform. 
  • :30 minutes | TikTok Trends
    • Pull out your phones and get ready to share theTRENDS that you have been seeing on the platform. 
      • Remember: What I see on my FYP will be different from what you see on your FYP - so let's share!

MATERIALS:
  • TikTok Trends doc
  • Archive of past office hours recordings
  • TikTok Drive

If there are any questions/topics that were not discussed during office hours, submit a ticket to Partnerships [here] and we'll get back to you (:

See you soon! Love,
Partnerships

Subject: [Info Session 2 of 2] The Championship 2023!
Description:
Topic: [Info Session 2 of 2] The Championship 2023!
Time: Feb 2, 2023 02:00 London

Join Zoom Meeting
https://vaynerx.zoom.us/j/84274788477?pwd=ZFZWbGxXZ0NtVVh0NGdzMUpkSk81UT09

Meeting ID: 842 7478 8477
Passcode: 605244



We are thrilled to announce the relaunch and third round of our CHAMPIONSHIP PROGRAM for 2023! 

This is not your typical mentorship dynamic. ‘The Championship’ takes the foundation of mentorship—pairing people to learn from each other—and adds the focus of championing each other, both as individuals and as employees.

The foundation of this program is based on our DEI efforts, and is built for anyone and everyone who wants 1:1 connection and support. Know that by being a Champion of others, you will in turn be Championed. It’s a win-win.

This year, we are building a program which allows for multiple opportunities to engage and participate depending on one's interest, goals, and commitment intentions. 

These options are:

  • Committed Mentorship to be placed  in a mentor/mentee pairing based on interests
    • minimum commitment of monthly recurring meeting cadence for a 6 month cycle, up to 12 months
    • must have at least 1 year of tenure with VaynerX to participate
  • Connections and introductions across VaynerX based on interests and areas of opportunity
    • no fixed meeting cadence
    • no minimum tenure to participate
Please reach out to the Championship team (championship@vaynerx.com) with any questions!

Subject: The Industry Bulletin [Retail]
Description:
The Industry Bulletin will be a monthly deep dive into key industry verticals for teams to join and engage in an open forum to share:

  • New briefs/priority focus for the upcoming quarter

  • Identify pain points and areas of opportunity

  • Identify key internal/external touch points and ideation opportunities for team osmosis


Partnerships will lead with additional support to generate discussion and provide proactive recommendations. This allows us to get even closer to the D2D ongoings with accounts, while providing a runway for teams to share what's coming down the pipeline in the macro.
The sessions will cover the Retail, Auto, CPG and B2B verticals and cycle through each in the same order month over month. -::~:~::~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~::~:~::- Join with Google Meet: https://meet.google.com/sze-pevr-zyn Or dial: (US) +1 402-862-6130 PIN: 447509912# More phone numbers: https://tel.meet/sze-pevr-zyn?pin=3607352938208&hs=7 Learn more about Meet at: https://support.google.com/a/users/answer/9282720 Please do not edit this section. -::~:~::~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~:~::~:~::-

Subject: [Who, What, Why?] HOW TO BUY NETFLIX 101 (via Xandr DSP)
Description:
Microsoft Teams meeting

Join on your computer, mobile app or room device:

Click here to join the meeting<https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19%3ameeting_NGYzOTJmNWEtNThkYi00M2E2LWJmNWMtM2Q3MWVjMGNjN2E0%40thread.v2/0?context=%7b%22Tid%22%3a%2272f988bf-86f1-41af-91ab-2d7cd011db47%22%2c%22Oid%22%3a%227969c043-7ccb-4a55-8ab5-1de4c1c8c52b%22%7d>

Meeting ID: 280 437 951 392

Passcode: YvvFst

Download Teams<https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-teams/download-app> | Join on the web<https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-teams/join-a-meeting>


It is with great excitement that we announce our 4th [Who, What, Why?] programming session, this time focusing on one of the hottest new-to-ad-placement platforms: NETFLIX.


ICYMI, Netflix announced an ad-supported membership tier in Q4 ‘23, bringing ads into the streaming platform for the first time.


Netflix has partnered exclusively with Microsoft to purchase the ads via Xandr DSP, and this session will be aimed at educating all teams on how exactly we can buy this inventory, as well as what audience and measurement solutions look like.

As always, attendance is strongly encouraged for all VaynerX employees, and this session will be recorded for those who cannot make it.

Questions? Please reach out to partnerships@vaynermedia.com.

Subject: Open Enrollment is happening right now!
Description:
Hi team, as a reminder, our VaynerX Open Enrollment period is now open from Wednesday, March 8th and will close EOD EST on Wednesday, March 22nd! All benefits elected during this time will be effective April 1, 2023 through March 31, 2024. 



Open Enrollment is the period in which all full-time, eligible employees can elect, re-elect, enroll or waive our Company sponsored health insurance plans. This is the one and ONLY time that you can make changes to your benefits including the plans you are enrolled in, adding new coverages, and electing more FSA/DCA dollars outside of major qualifying life events (i.e. marriage, loss of external coverage, birth/adoption of a child). This process is simple and will be done directly through the ADP benefits portal!

Subject: Final Day of Open Enrollment
Description:
OPEN ENROLLMENT ENDS TODAY, MARCH 22ND AT EOD EST! Unless you experience a Qualifying Life Event (i.e. turning 26/loss of external coverage, marriage, birth/adoption of a child, etc.), this will be the ONLY opportunity you have to add and/or make changes to your benefit elections for the 2023-2024 benefit year. No exceptions will be made to make changes after open enrollment is completed without experiencing a qualifying life event. 

Please head over to the ADP enrollment wizard if you'd like to:
  • enroll in coverage for the first time
  • make any changes to your current coverages or plans
  • add/remove dependents
  • participate in FSA or DCA (regardless of whether you're currently enrolled as your current enrollment will not carryover to the new year for these benefits)
  • increase, enroll or drop any of our voluntary employee-paid benefits

IMPORTANT! If any of the above situations apply to you, you will need to proceed through the enrollment wizard in ADP, regardless of whether or not you are making changes to your medical/dental/vision elections.

Alternatively, if you're currently enrolled in medical, dental and/or vision, and DO NOT want to make any additions or changes to your 2023-2024 benefit elections, no further action is required.

Description:
On behalf of the VaynerConsulting Leadership Team, it is with much excitement that I officially invite you to the 2023 VMNY Consulting Team Offsite.

There has been such tremendous growth in this department and even more great things to come. We will use this time together, IN PERSON, to immerse ourselves in what it means to be on the consulting team, all the offerings we provide to both our clients and the VX organization, and celebrate the great work that you all do each & every day.

Please join us for an overview of our updated Functional Competencies for Analytics across all disciplines/levels, as we work to create a common language for what success looks like at VaynerMedia via our Core Competencies.

Notes: 
  • This session will be recorded for anyone with unavoidable conflicts, but please do your best to join live.
  • If you have any questions, please reach out to Anna Norman (anorman@vaynermedia.com). Thanks!


As a reminder, Functional Competencies are:

  • The technical skills needed to succeed in your role.

  • WHAT you need to know in order to perform your job.


Understanding our Foundational and Functional Competencies will allow us all to: 

  • Set and mutually understand expectations and identify growth opportunities.

  • Have a key tool for guiding feedback conversations/HiBob Check-Ins.

  • Focus recruiting efforts to identify new talent.

Subject: [SAP] Internal Debrief
Description:
Debriefing following Playbook preso to SAP clients 





  • 1. Are all aligned/know our marching orders for the feedback loop?
    • Are we all aligned with how we are bringing opportunities and briefing them
    • are we all aligned on how strategy and creative will review cc's before they go to client
    • are we all aligned on the format we are sending assets to clients

    2. Do we all know the process for amplification? If something goes viral, what are our steps:
    • Are we all aligned on the key kPIS we’re using to make decisions, and we know the process to discuss when to act
    • Do we all know how to stack (i.e., make more assets like the one that’s working)
    • How do we communicate to the client
    • When do we decide to bridge

    3. Are we aligned on the cadence/process to build out reporting? 
    • Is everyone aware of the steps to get to the bi-weekly and their role in it (strategy/analytics owning)
    • Is everyone aware of the steps to get to the monthly report, and what they are on the hook for
    • Does everyone know when we are looking at performance

  • Hayley to share guidance for considerations for reporting and client management 
  • Live feedback we received

Subject: Roblox Educational Session for VaynerX - Organized by Vayner3
Description:
Join the Vayner3 team for an exciting and interactive Roblox training session designed to give you everything you need to know about the wonderful world of Roblox. 


Vayner has been named one of Roblox's inaugural agency partners, and we're thrilled to bring this opportunity to clients across VX. In this training you will:
  1. Get an overview of the Roblox platform and its vast creative capabilities.
  2. Discover strategies to engage players and the thriving Roblox community.
  3. Explore case studies from leading marketers.
  4. Gain insights into Roblox's new advertising strategies (#ImmersiveAds).
  5. Learn about how we can help bring this new opportunity to Vayner clients.


Whether you're a seasoned Roblox enthusiast or new to the platform, join us!

Subject: The Industry Bulletin [Auto]
Description:

Subject: [TikTok] Office Hours
Description:
Hi All,

You are all invited to attend TikTok Office Hours! This is a safe space for everyone and anyone to share any observations that they've noticed on the platform, ask questions, and even brainstorm - so come join the party at the Zoom link below and let's talk about all things Tok-related.

Join Zoom Meeting: https://vaynerx.zoom.us/j/8491633269
________________________________________________________
AGENDA:
  • :30 minutes | All Things TikTok: observations, Q&A, brainstorming, etc..
    • An open floor for anybody to ask questions, brainstorm with the group, share wins, and state any observations that are happening on the platform. 
  • :30 minutes | TikTok Trends
    • Pull out your phones and get ready to share theTRENDS that you have been seeing on the platform. 
      • Remember: What I see on my FYP will be different from what you see on your FYP - so let's share!

MATERIALS:
  • TikTok Trends doc
  • Archive of past office hours recordings
  • TikTok Drive

If there are any questions/topics that were not discussed during office hours, submit a ticket to Partnerships [here] and we'll get back to you (:

See you soon! Love,
